For? <p>Inherit <code>Attributes</code> and <code>Methods</code> from Base class (parent) to Derived class (child).</p> Grammar? <p>Use the <code>:</code> symbol.</p> Let's do it! <p>Problem: Let the <code>Car</code> class (child) inherits the Attributes and Methods from the <code>Vehicle</code> class (parent):</p> inher_base.c++<pre><code>#include &lt;iostream&gt;
#include &lt;string&gt;
#include &lt;assert.h&gt; 
